Independent read-only review findings preserved before correction:
- Worker produced a bare SHA-256 digest while SQL required sha256:<64 lowercase hex>.
- Offer loading used only the activation-time aggregate and could not see a later SQL Interest.
- A NO_WAITING receipt could collide with a later dispatch for the unchanged Slot.
- Inbox payload_hash contained the idempotency key and was not verified on replay.
- Queue public seed was trusted from the message instead of checked against locked authority.
- The applied 0003 migration had been edited, producing schema drift in the existing test database.
- The old Hold uniqueness predicate prohibited historical Slot reuse.
- The 0003 down migration failed on an Answer-first ReviewWindow.
- Legacy and Answer-first allocation did not yet share the same Q_i=1 lease/lock.
- Terminal Queue Worker failure was not visible as an explicit platform event.

